==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/hʌ̃/}}
* {{audio|en-us-huh.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ʌ}}

===Interjection===
{{en-interj}}

# {{context|with falling pitch}} {{n-g|used to express [[amusement]] or subtle [[surprise]].}}
#: '''''Huh!'''  I'm sure I locked it when I left.''
# {{n-g|Used to express [[doubt]] or [[confusion]].}}
#: '''''Huh?''' Where did they go?''
# {{context|with rising pitch}} {{n-g|Used to [[reinforce]] a [[question]].}}
#: ''Where were you last night?  '''Huh'''?''
# {{rft-sense}} {{slang|with falling pitch}} {{n-g|Used either to [[belittle]] the issuer of a statement/question, or [[sarcasm|sarcastically]] to indicate utter agreement, and that the statement being responded to is an extreme [[understatement]]. The intonation is changed to distinguish between the two meanings - implied [[dullness]] for belittlement, and [[feigned]] [[surprise]] for utter agreement.}}
#: ''(belittlement)'' A:"''We should go to an amusement park, it would be fun.''" B:"'''''Huh.'''''"
#: ''(agreement)'' A""''Murder is bad.''" B:"'''''Huh!'''''"
# {{informal|with rising pitch}} {{n-g|Used to indicate that one did not hear what was said.}}
#: '''''Huh'''?  Could you speak up?''
# {{informal|with falling pitch}} {{n-g|Used to create a [[tag question]].}}
#: ''It's getting kind of late, '''huh?'''''

